race.comment: BEYOND MY KEN (3) resumed much improved as expected when beaten a nose at Taree over this distance and then progressed nicely last time scoring as a $2.3 favourite over 900m at Scone. Well placed with the 2kg claim and he can take the next step. THIS ONE TIME (11) is a leader who led and deserved her comfortable win here at CL3 level. Has an awkward gate today but is a decent chance to repeat. TOUGH GUY (9) is back from a spell and is proven fresh. Wasn't far away here last time seeking the hat-trick off easy wins and has plenty of scope for improvement. Uses the low gate and Bullock's engagement is a decent push for his chances. A player. LIGHTNING SPEED (10) resumes and is also good fresh. She has won all three runs here and Heywood will likely push forward from the sticky gate. May find this a touch short, but has to be kept onside.
